Blog - Has your company growth stalled? You may be in the Overview About Us Focus Blog Contact × Overview About Us Focus Blog Contact Featured, Ionic Partners Has your company growth stalled? You may be in the Blog by Andy Tryba October , 0 You remember it like Your company’s revenue had Growth had Things that worked before just You were Geoffrey Moore states that your company fell into ‘The Chasm’. In his iconic book ‘Crossing the Chasm’, he describes how the ‘smooth’ Technology Adoption Curve is a bit The Technology Adoption Curve All companies & technologies ride the Rogers Technology Adoption curve . The curve describes the adoption of technology across different market Some customers are willing to be on the ‘bleeding edge’ and others will only adopt a proven This Technology Adoption Curve is broken up into 5 market Innovators – the first to adopt new technologies, they are a small but passionate set of folks that love tech Early Adopters – the second group is a slightly larger group that is also generally and highly adaptable to new They embrace new products after the Early Majority – the third group is a much larger group that is a bit more careful than the previous 2 They are still willing to adopt new technologies – but only after the Early Adopter and Innovators have proven the technology to be Late Majority – the fourth group is a conservative and They need a bit of convincing before investing in something Laggards – the last group is an extremely frugal, very conservative and These folks still have rotary dial The Chasm Moore states that there is a ‘chasm’ between the Early Adopters and the Early This is due to the fact that the expectations of the first 2 groups are very different than the last To effectively ‘Cross the Chasm’ – companies need to ‘pivot’ their product offerings to address the mainstream A ‘whole product’ is required for a technology to cross the chasm into the mainstream of the For those companies that do manage to get across the chasm – good days are typically in the The company is now into the ‘Early Majority’ – which is a much larger part of the Often times, the company will double or triple in revenue with strong Awesome… But what happens after that? When you relook at the Technology Adoption Curve – and zoom at the top of the curve – you notice something As you climb up the Early Majority, the slope of the curve starts to It then eventually becomes flat! In business terms – this means the awesome revenue growth that you experienced after crossing the chasm starts to It then completely This stall comes out of nowhere – since you’ve been experiencing great growth over the past several And as time goes on, unfortunately, revenue then starts to According to ScaleVP – you can predict this growth After analyzing thousands of SaaS companies – the ‘predictable decay’ of next year’s growth will be % of this year’s And for many software companies – growth under % per year results in only an 8% chance of surviving a few more years ( SaaS sales benchmark ) But I thought this was supposed to be the good ole’ times? You worked hard to cross Geoffrey Moore’s chasm – what’s going on here??? The 2 nd Chasm What’s happening here is actually an important missing part of Moore’s Believe it or not – there are actually 2 chasms! Wait – what? The first chasm gets startups to the mainstream For many software companies – revenues go from $0 to $3-5m a Getting to millions a year in revenue is incredibly But as predicted by the adoption curve and predictable decay – revenue growth gets harder and harder every Deals that appear to be ‘just around the corner’ delay The technical debt on your product expands while your next generation product just can’t seem to Your investor’s IPO dreams are being Your employees are starting to wonder if this rocket ship isn’t going to pay for their future yacht after You’re now in the 2 nd By definition – the 2 nd Chasm is a bit further in a company’s Revenues have often grown to $8-$10m year – but have been hovering at that level for several And similar to the first chasm, companies require significant changes to get across this new chasm to regain But unfortunately – this 2 nd Chasm is much much harder to exit than the Why is it harder to cross the 2 nd Chasm? Companies that fall into the 2 nd Chasm have often been in business for They’ve done a great job getting across the first chasm and addressing a portion of the mainstream But crossing the 2 nd Chasm is harder than the first due 3 primary reasons: Company processes are more established and rigid: Think of these companies as middle Not quite as nimble or flexible as they were when they were a few years And as a result, the process and procedures that have been in place for a decade are now incredibly hard to Product development has been going on for years: You’d think that the more ‘mature’ product would be better equipped to handle But more often than not – since the product was originally built years ago – it

Cookie Policy for HealerPlus × This is the Cookie Policy for HealerPlus, accessible from https: healerplus.com ​ What Are Cookies ​ As is common practice with almost all professional websites this site uses cookies, which are tiny files that are downloaded to your computer, to improve your This page describes what information they gather, how we use it and why we sometimes need to store these We will also share how you can prevent these cookies from being stored however this may downgrade or break certain elements of the sites ​ For more general information on cookies see the Wikipedia article on HTTP ​ How We Use Cookies ​ We use cookies for a variety of reasons detailed Unfortunately in most cases there are no industry standard options for disabling cookies without completely disabling the functionality and features they add to this It is recommended that you leave on all cookies if you are not sure whether you need them or not in case they are used to provide a service that you ​ Disabling Cookies ​ You can prevent the setting of cookies by adjusting the settings on your browser (see your browser Help for how to do this). Be aware that disabling cookies will affect the functionality of this and many other websites that you Disabling cookies will usually result in also disabling certain functionality and features of the this Therefore it is recommended that you do not disable ​ The Cookies We Set ​ ​ Account related cookies If you create an account with us then we will use cookies for the management of the signup process and general These cookies will usually be deleted when you log out however in some cases they may remain afterwards to remember your site preferences when logged ​ Login related cookies We use cookies when you are logged in so that we can remember this This prevents you from having to log in every single time you visit a new These cookies are typically removed or cleared when you log out to ensure that you can only access restricted features and areas when logged ​ Email newsletters related cookies This site offers newsletter or email subscription services and cookies may be used to remember if you are already registered and whether to show certain notifications which might only be valid to subscribed unsubscribed ​ Orders processing related cookies This site offers or payment facilities and some cookies are essential to ensure that your order is remembered between pages so that we can process it ​ Surveys related cookies From time to time we offer user surveys and questionnaires to provide you with interesting insights, helpful tools, or to understand our user base more These surveys may use cookies to remember who has already taken part in a survey or to provide you with accurate results after you change ​ Forms related cookies When you submit data to through a form such as those found on contact pages or comment forms cookies may be set to remember your user details for future ​ Site preferences cookies In order to provide you with a great experience on this site we provide the functionality to set your preferences for how this site runs when slavery and supports efforts to eradicate such Resolve Surgical Technologies would never knowingly conduct business with contractors or suppliers engaged in such Given the nature of the types of products, implants and services we provide, it is our assessment that our business activities present little risk of promoting human trafficking and With respect to these issues, the California Transparency in the Supply Chains Act of (the “Act”) requires certain manufacturers and retailers, including Resolve Surgical Technologies, to disclose their efforts to eradicate human trafficking and slavery from their supply The Act requires disclosure in five (5) areas: audits, verification, certification, training, and internal At this time, Resolve Surgical Technologies does not audit or independently verify its product supply chain or its direct suppliers for risks relating to human trafficking or According to the Resolve Surgical Technologies Code of Conduct and our contractual arrangements with suppliers, our suppliers are required to comply with applicable laws and regulations governing their business Failure to comply with these contractual requirements constitutes breach of contract, but there is no separate certification process specifically for slavery and human Resolve Surgical Technologies has incorporated information on addressing the potential for human Frequently Asked Questions — Eternally 0 Skip to Content Home Providers Providers How We Partner About Us Who We Are What We Do Our Leadership Resources FAQs Plan Ahead Informational Video Careers How we Open Menu Close Menu Home Providers Providers How We Partner About Us Who We Are What We Do Our Leadership Resources FAQs Plan Ahead Informational Video Careers How we Open Menu Close Menu Home Folder: Providers Back Providers How We Partner Folder: About Us Back Who We Are What We Do Our Leadership Folder: Resources Back Current Page: FAQs Plan Ahead Informational Video Careers How we Frequently Asked Questions + What does Eternally do? Eternally connects with you over the phone or on a video Eternally is your guide to Advance Care Planning (ACP) in every This involves discussing and documenting your treatment preferences in a difficult It’s there to guide your loved ones and ensure that if you’re unable to speak for yourself, your family and doctors will know your Eternally will explain the scenarios for which having control over the type of care you receive is The topics you should consider include who you might want to have speak on your behalf if you cannot speak for yourself, what types of treatments you may or may not want, and generally, what is important to your quality of If you already talked about this with your doctor, that’s great, but we’re still here to + Why have so many turned to Eternally already? Eternally is unlike any other service for Advance Care Our Care Team members meet you where you are, and spend as much time as you need explaining your options until you’re Our clinicians have years of experience walking patients through their questions and are here to + What is an Advance Directive and why do I need one? Anyone at any age may unexpectedly be in a position where they cannot speak for themselves, such as an accident or severe In these situations, having your treatment preferences written down assures that your doctor knows the kind of care you want and or knows who the person is that you want to make decisions on your Eternally will help you navigate your choices for your future care, and help you document your decisions in a document called an Advance An Advance Directive acts as a Your loved ones and family members can look through this document and easily understand the type of care you want to By naming a healthcare proxy, you delegate the to one This reduces your family’s stress and strain during a tough and trying time because they can know that their decisions align with what you would + What types of questions are in an Advance Directive? If you cannot speak for yourself, only you know what treatment you would like to If music relaxes you, or having friends and family with you is important to you, these are the types of details you can include in your Advance Directive and examples of what can be Additionally, it is important to decide what treatment means to you, and if there could be a point when you may not wish to receive For example, if you would be dependent on An Advance Directive contains two different types of The first type of question is about the healthcare you would like to This includes questions such as would you like to receive CPR, dialysis, or antibiotics, who you want as your healthcare proxy, and if you want treatment if you are in a coma or have severe brain The second section is about personal preferences such as comfort, how you want to be treated, and what you want your loved ones to know about your This section includes questions such as do you want to be kept clean, do you want music playing in your room, and if you want to be buried or You can see an example Advance Directive here (which is legal and used in out of states). + What types of healthcare treatment may I include in my document? You may include wishes that align with your cultural or spiritual beliefs, your medical treatment preference, or how you want to be remembered after you Eternally helps you capture what is important to you so that you can share your wishes with your loved ones and your care Each section is optional, so you can create a custom document to reflect your unique + How do I make my document legal? Advance Care Planning documents are commonly referred to as a “Living Will”, “Durable Power of Attorney”, or “Advance Directive”. Different states have differing requirements to make these documents Generally, once the document is signed by the principal, and witnessed according to state guidelines (usually two adult witnesses and or notarized), it is legally Please note that Eternally does not provide legal Please consult with legal counsel for specific direction if you have concerns about the legal status of this + What is a healthcare proxy, and what is their role? A health care proxy (also known as an agent or surrogate) is a person that you trust to make decisions about your medical care, including tests, medications, and surgeries—but only if you’re unable to speak

Login Cancel Register for an account Lunar Account Registration 1 - Account Info 2 - Reseller Certificate 3 - Publisher Discounts Thank you for your interest in registering with Lunar Please complete the required fields Username Password Confirm password First Name Last Name Company Name Email Address Continue Cancel Contact Us: ©2021   FAQ - Lunar Distribution Login Register Username Password Forgot password? Login Cancel Register for an account FAQ How do I open an account? Go to Click on register for an account Create a username and password Provide First name and Last Name for the main account contact Company Name Email address Please note that this email address will be receiving all communication from This includes invoice, shipment tracking and all FOC Product If your state does not have a sales tax, or you are outside the US, please check the box “not subject to sales tax”. If your state has a sales tax, we require a resale certificate, and you will receive an email from Avalara that will walk you through the process of filling out the certificate and submitting In most cases, a sales tax permit or license is not a resale While you may submit that, we will still require a resale certificate to be on You will then need to fill out your UCS Diamond account number and UCS account email to verify your discount for Hit Complete Registration Once that’s You’ll be sent an email from to verify your email Once the email is verified you can log into your You will then need to create a “store” under the main If you have multiple stores, you’ll need to create an account for each store that you want to receive If you want all your books sent to one location, I would just create one “store” You can always add more stores Once this is completed, you may place Please note: Nothing will be shipped until your resale certificate is How do I order? To place an order please go to the New Order Tab For your first order we suggest you create an initial On this page, it will show you any existing orders you currently You have several views to search for Detail View is a broad overview of all products with images for most product Order Entry Product List Entry where there are 3 filter Box #1 is Order Due This will give you the upcoming FOC date as well as the next Initial order Box #2 contains the upcoming FOC Box #3 is Date and is currently where you will also find already released To the right is a search that will pull up products as you CSV Upload is where you can upload a CSV file of your orders and you can also download many different forms of CSV files for the product Delimited Text, which can be used if you are copy and pasting a group of codes and quantities from a Then, click the “Continue to Review” Orders placed during the Initial Order or FOC window will overwrite current orders in the Any orders placed outside those two windows will add to your Also, all orders placed on the Lunar site by OTHER methods such as by keying in an order or uploading an order will ADD to any previously existing order Make sure that you don t potentially double up on With all 3 options, you will click the “Continue to Review” button and then confirm the You should receive an email with an order If you do not receive this email, your order has not been Once an order is confirmed, you can adjust any items up to the FOC for those If you place a new separate order, any items ordered are in addition to any previous orders How do I reorder product once the FOC has passed? As long as quantities are available and the items have released, items ordered after the FOC date will be sent in the next scheduled If you place an order for items before the FOC date, and then another quantity after, then the first quantity will be sent in the release week and the second may be sent in the following week’s This depends on the amount of time between the FOC deadline and the amount of orders If the system notes the orders after the FOC deadline as backordered, the items may not all fill in the release How can I place a reorder for already released items? Click the New Order link and use the Product List Entry and click the Date and scroll to the past If you want to see everything that has released, click all the past The system is set up to add any reorders placed up until Thursday midnight to the following weeks In the coming month, we will be receiving the top collected editions and will make those available for order as soon as they are received and uploaded into the What are my shipping costs? We have negotiated very competitive rates with FedEx and all shipments are sent by FedEx The normal transit times for FedEx range from Due to the current pandemic, shipping times have become We strive to get product out as quickly as possible to you but there may be delays due to the Rates start at $7.25. We can also ship items by UPS, but the rates are not quite as competitive and

Actress and vegan activist Alicia Silverstone has had it with the vegan milk surcharge at In a recent letter the actress posted to her blog The Kind Life, Silverstone explained that she, along with other activists such as Alan Cumming, have been asking Starbucks to drop its vegan milk surcharge for many years as the extra charge makes more environmentally and options less accessible to the “These charges may seem small, but they penalize customers who are making humane and environmentally friendly choices,” Silverstone “It also penalizes people for issues they can’t control, like being lactose intolerant—which affects percent of the population, predominantly people of ” Silverstone renewed her demand—which she made public in on Twitter—after the coffee chain released its sustainability plan, which CEO Kevin Johnson announced after an audit found that dairy was responsible for the majority of the chain’s global carbon Starbucks has made recent advancements in adding beverages and foods to its In March, Starbucks expanded Oatly’s oat milk to its nationwide menu—and, due to several factors, including unexpected customer demand, is now experiencing shortages of the vegan And while the menu additions are a step in the right direction, Silverstone says it’s time for the chain to evaluate its stance on charging more for vegan Debunking Starbuck’s reasons for vegan milk surcharges Silverstone debunked Starbucks’ claim that it must charge extra for vegan milk—typically $.50 or more per cup—due to the higher cost it pays for milk as compared to dairy, pointing out that Starbucks’ profit margin on a cup of plain coffee is “With such a margin per cup of coffee, even after overhead, it is not an unreasonable request to stop charging for milk,” Silverstone wrote, adding the “true cost” of milk is greater than market prices due to subsidies the animal agriculture industry receives that keep prices artificially “If the true cost of milk were reflected by its carbon impact alone, it would cost far more than the surcharge we’re forced to pay on the sustainable alternative,” Silverstone The longtime vegan actress also debunked an argument Starbucks has made about charging extra for all modifications, explaining that lack of standard vegan options on the permanent menu penalizes customers for modifying their drinks with “If Starbucks hopes to meet its goal of reducing percent of its carbon emissions, water use, and waste by , then an obvious first step is to ensure that the environmentally friendly options are accessible to everyone by lowering the price of their options, and not penalizing those of us who are already choosing the sustainable, kind products,” Silverstone This Woman Turned Down $1 Million on Shark Tank She’s Now Selling 1 Million Pounds of Vegan Fried Chicken on April , at 9:00 pm Vegan fried chicken company Atlas Monroe is set to become the largest manufacturer of vegan chicken in the The news comes as Atlas Monroe recently acquired its own manufacturing plant at a , warehouse in San Diego, CA, with plans to open a second location this With the expansion, Atlas Monroe founder Deborah Torres has maintained ownership of the company since her appearance on reality investment show Shark In , she was offered $1 million (an amount rarely offered on the show) from investor Mark Cuban and guest investor Rohan Oza for percent of the Torres turned down that offer because she did not want to give up her brand because she believed the company would soon generate the same amount on its “The fact you guys are even offering a million dollars lets me know you do understand what we are worth,” Torres said on the Vegan fried chicken for all Since then, Atlas Monroe has reached over $2 million in sales through its website, fulfilled tens of thousands of orders, and expanded to manufacturing vegan bacon, applewood smoked ribs, and stuffed turkeys, signature sauces, and bakery items such as sweet potato and chocolate With the new manufacturing plant,

Takes any number of beats per measure, for your odd meters Configure a beat value from a whole note to a note! You can even change the tempo marking! (ex: dotted quarter = tempo) Quick save buttons to store your most common tempos Continuous playback even when changing the settings Looking into the Future We want musicians to take their sessions to the next level and double their efficiency through No need to stop and reset your metronome on meter changes, this will be an issue of the past! Some features to expect in Ver 2: Program your entire piece or solo into the app Simple, easy, efficient input menus Rehearse specific sections, or the entire piece Share your programs on the cloud for ! Accelerandos, Ritardandos, what else can we add? About the project This project was originally inspired by the tried and true Beat This is a very robust metronome that can literally do anything you throw at However, a colleague of mine expressed how repetitive and time consuming the process of programming it Thus the project Musicians Aide was born! The goal right out of the gate is to make this metronome the most efficient practice tool on the market! This starts right down to the first Not only will version 1 be completely free (plus Ad free), it hopefully will also rival other paid apps out on the market right now! The next goal is to try to capture the essence of the Beat into a simpler and easy to use metronome We will tackle the challenge of making complete programmability in as little user actions as possible, and including enough features to double your productivity in the practice room! Available now on the Google Play Store! Do Americans have shared goals? Help us find We are connecting millions of Americans to take The Unify Challenge with a partner, over a live video Take the Unify Challenge Can we learn to work together? Imagine hundreds of thousands, and eventually, millions of us, over the course of a year, spending time reviewing clear and engaging material to learn about ALL the different ways we could solve for one of our shared Can we build consensus? Imagine getting together regularly to discuss those options in small groups with other Americans, where there is likely to be a diversity of And, like sitting on a jury, the point is not to win arguments, but to reach Can we implement our consensus? And then imagine, once millions of us converge on a plan to achieve a shared goal, we then carry our shared solution into the political arena, with a grassroots lobbying force like this country has never That is how we can move our country forward The End Goal Can we replace politics with problem solving? American democracy is dying from our low People can’t see a way out of the juvenile and way we govern We want to demonstrate that there is a way out . CarbonScope available now – The Climate Solutions Blog Skip to content The Climate Solutions Blog CleanMetrics Menu Contact us Contact us CarbonScope available now When we launched CleanMetrics at the beginning of , we started with a It has been clear that businesses of all sizes can do a lot to address climate But before they can cut their emissions, they need to know where they stand without spending a ton of money and In the brave new world of low emissions, carbon modeling and emissions accounting should be fast, easy and inexpensive . This was the motivation for kicking off an intense period of software development and road We are finally at a point where our new flagship carbon modeling tool, CarbonScope , is ready for users . As we architected this web app, we recognized that the same framework would serve two common, but often distinct, carbon modeling applications equally well: corporate greenhouse gas inventory analyses and product So CarbonScope does both, using a shared inventory database and a shared modeling The design is simple and minimalistic, and the functionality is easy to use and CarbonScope comes packaged with an hour of training videos designed to get new users off to a fast Annual subscriptions start at just $300 for commercial Check out our pricing page for consultant, teaching research and student for climate carbon app developers – The Climate Solutions Blog Skip to content The Climate Solutions Blog CleanMetrics Menu Contact us Contact us API for climate carbon app developers As app developers, our primary focus at CleanMetrics has been on tools and apps that businesses and organizations can use to quantify, track and reduce their climate We have been increasingly hearing from other app developers looking to integrate a inventory (LCI) database with their These apps typically let consumers track their personal carbon emissions from purchases and other The idea is to help consumers become in their purchasing decisions and or make it easy for them to offset their We are now releasing an API to our LCI database, CarbonScopeData , to address the lack of carbon emissions data that plagues many We want to help improve the quality of climate and carbon apps across board, and thereby empower consumers to take decisive action to slow climate The CarbonScopeData API is a RESTful web service that provides access to both process LCI and environmentally extended LCI The process LCI dataset contains over materials, products and processes, including the largest commercially available LCI database for North American food production and The LCI dataset uses data on economic transactions between industry sectors to provide data for US goods and services covering the entire US The database provides three key life cycle metrics: greenhouse gas emissions (embodied carbon), primary energy use (embodied energy) and water use (embodied virtual water). As usual, our pricing structure is designed to reduce barriers and make emissions accounting as widespread as We require an annual subscription and purchase of API accesses sold in blocks of ,000 100,000 500,000 Please let us know if you have any questions!
